{"page_id": 55530, "slug": "Evangelion_Unit-02_(Anima)", "title": "Evangelion Unit-02 (Anima)", "display_title": "<span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">Evangelion Unit-02 (Anima)</span>", "namespace": 0, "content_model": "wikitext", "language": null, "wikitext": "<span style=\"font-size:200%\"><code>[[Evangelion Unit-02|NGE]]</code> <code>[[Evangelion Unit-02 (NTE)|NTE]]</code> <code>'''Anima'''</code> <code>[[Evangelion Unit-02 (Other)|Other]]</code></span>\n{{Expand}}\n{{Stub}}\n\n{{Evangelion Rebuild Infobox\n| name          = Evangelion Unit-02\n| image         = [[Image:Anima 02.png|center|225px]]\n| japanese      = エヴァンゲリオン２号機\n| model         = Production Model\n| nation        = Germany (E.U.)\n| organization  = [[Nerv]]\n| pilots        = [[Asuka Langley Soryu]]\n| upgrades      = [[Evangelion Unit-02 Stage II]]<br> [[Unit 02 Stage II Allegorica]]<br> [[Unit 02 Type F]]<br> [[Crimson A1]]<br> [[Torwartα1]]\n| unique        = \n| debut         = [[ANIMA|Backstory of Anima Vol.1]]\n| status        = Unclear\n}}\nIn [[ANIMA|Evangelion Anima]], Unit-02 was upgraded into [[Evangelion Unit-02 Stage II|Unit-02 Stage II]] before the start of the story. Much like [[Evangelion Unit-02|its NGE counterpart]], this version of Unit-02 also faced off against the Mass Production Evas; however, unlike its TV counterpart, it was chosen by [[Seele]] as trigger for Third Impact and fought alongside [[Evangelion Unit-01 Type F|Unit-01 Type F]] and [[Evangelion Unit-00 Type F|Unit-00 Type F]], and therefore survives the battle.\n\n{{Evangelion List}}\n[[Category:A to Z]]\n[[Category:Evangelions]]", "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><span style=\"font-size:200%\"><code><a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-02\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02\">NGE</a></code> <code><a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-02_(NTE)\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02 (NTE)\">NTE</a></code> <code><b>Anima</b></code> <code><a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-02_(Other)\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02 (Other)\">Other</a></code></span>\n</p>\n<table align=\"center\" style=\"border:2px solid lightseagreen; width:85%; background:honeydew;\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:Eva2-22_C0750.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/c/ce/Eva2-22_C0750.jpg/180px-Eva2-22_C0750.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"180\" height=\"101\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/c/ce/Eva2-22_C0750.jpg/270px-Eva2-22_C0750.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/c/ce/Eva2-22_C0750.jpg/360px-Eva2-22_C0750.jpg 2x\" /></a></span>\n</td>\n<td style=\"text-align:center;\">\n<p><big><b>\"<i>Making something... Nurturing something is really great. You can see and learn so many things from the process.</i>\"</b></big><br />\nPlease help improve this article or section by <b>expanding it.</b><br />\n<small>If you have questions on what to improve/expand, please discuss on the talk page.</small>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br clear=\"all\" />\n<i>This article bears the unpleasant designation of \"<b>Stub</b>.\" This is a <b>Bad Thing</b>. Provide a great service to NGE fan-geeks everywhere by <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://wiki.evageeks.org/index.php?title=Evangelion_Unit-02_(Anima)&amp;action=edit\">making it awesomer!</a></i>\n<br clear=\"all\" />\n</p><p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width: 30%; text-align: left; font-size: 90%;\" cellspacing=\"2\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background: greenyellow; font-size: 120%;\" align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\"><b>Evangelion Unit-02</b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\"><figure class=\"mw-halign-center\" typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:Anima_02.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/7/70/Anima_02.png/225px-Anima_02.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"225\" height=\"379\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/70/Anima_02.png/338px-Anima_02.png 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/70/Anima_02.png/450px-Anima_02.png 2x\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"background: greenyellow; font-size: 120%;\" align=\"center\" colspan=\"2\"><b>エヴァンゲリオン２号機</b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Model Type\n</th>\n<td>Production Model\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Nation of Origin\n</th>\n<td>Germany (E.U.)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Affiliation\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Nerv\" title=\"Nerv\">Nerv</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pilot(s)\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/Asuka_Langley_Soryu\" title=\"Asuka Langley Soryu\">Asuka Langley Soryu</a>\n</td></tr>\n\n\n\n<tr>\n<th>Upgrades/Variants\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/index.php?title=Evangelion_Unit-02_Stage_II&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02 Stage II (page does not exist)\">Evangelion Unit-02 Stage II</a><br /> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Unit_02_Stage_II_Allegorica&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Unit 02 Stage II Allegorica (page does not exist)\">Unit 02 Stage II Allegorica</a><br /> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Unit_02_Type_F&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Unit 02 Type F (page does not exist)\">Unit 02 Type F</a><br /> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Crimson_A1&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Crimson A1 (page does not exist)\">Crimson A1</a><br /> <a href=\"/index.php?title=Torwart%CE%B11&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Torwartα1 (page does not exist)\">Torwartα1</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Debut\n</th>\n<td><a href=\"/ANIMA\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ANIMA\">Backstory of Anima Vol.1</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Status\n</th>\n<td>Unclear\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><br />\nIn <a href=\"/ANIMA\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"ANIMA\">Evangelion Anima</a>, Unit-02 was upgraded into <a href=\"/index.php?title=Evangelion_Unit-02_Stage_II&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02 Stage II (page does not exist)\">Unit-02 Stage II</a> before the start of the story. Much like <a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-02\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02\">its NGE counterpart</a>, this version of Unit-02 also faced off against the Mass Production Evas; however, unlike its TV counterpart, it was chosen by <a href=\"/Seele\" title=\"Seele\">Seele</a> as trigger for Third Impact and fought alongside <a href=\"/index.php?title=Evangelion_Unit-01_Type_F&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-01 Type F (page does not exist)\">Unit-01 Type F</a> and <a href=\"/index.php?title=Evangelion_Unit-00_Type_F&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-00 Type F (page does not exist)\">Unit-00 Type F</a>, and therefore survives the battle.\n</p>\n<table class=\"infobox centered\" style=\"width: 60%; font-size: 90%; text-align: center; margin: 0 auto; clear: both\" align=\"center\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background: DarkSeaGreen; font-size: 110%;\"><i><b><a href=\"/Evangelions_(Portal)\" title=\"Evangelions (Portal)\">Evangelions</a></b></i>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/Evangelions\" title=\"Evangelions\">Evangelions</a> (general)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/Failed_Evangelion_Prototypes\" title=\"Failed Evangelion Prototypes\">Failed Evangelion Prototypes</a> | <a href=\"/Simulation_Bodies\" title=\"Simulation Bodies\">Simulation Bodies</a>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-00\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-00\">Eva-00</a> | <a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-01\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-01\">Eva-01</a> | <a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-02\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-02\">Eva-02</a> | <a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-03\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-03\">Eva-03</a> | <a href=\"/Evangelion_Unit-04\" title=\"Evangelion Unit-04\">Eva-04</a> | <a href=\"/Mass_Production_Evangelions\" title=\"Mass Production Evangelions\">Mass Production Evangelions</a> (Evas 05~13)\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><b><a href=\"/Rebuild_of_Evangelion\" title=\"Rebuild of Evangelion\">Rebuild of Evangelion</a></b>: <a href=\"/Evangelion_Mark.04\" title=\"Evangelion Mark.04\">Mark.04</a> | <a href=\"/Evangelion_U